</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Manufacturer: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline><span title="Click here to perform a search for all pinball games manufactured by 'Williams'"><a href="search.pl?searchtype=advanced&amp;mfgid=351">Williams Electronics, Incorporated (1967-1985) <i>[Trade Name: Williams</i>]</a></span></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Date Of Manufacture: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>June 27, 1977</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Model Number: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>474</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Type: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>Electro-mechanical (EM)&nbsp;<a href="showhelp.pl?item=type&amp;highlight=EM#EM" title="Show Type Classifications" target="help"><img alt="[?]" style="cursor: help;" src="/graphic/question.gif" border=0></a></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Production: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>1,300 units &nbsp;&nbsp;<font size="-1">(<i>confirmed</i>)</font></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" align="right" valign=baseline><b>Serial Number Database:</b></td><td colspan=4 align="left" valign=baseline><a href="redirect.pl?http://www.ipsnd.net/View.aspx?id=1251">View at <I>The Internet Pinball Serial Number Database</I> (IPSND.net)</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size="-1"><I>(External site)</i></font></td></tr><tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Theme: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>Sports - Horse Racing</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Notable Features: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline><a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Flipper">Flippers</a> (2), <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Pop_Bumper">Pop&nbsp;bumper</a> (1), <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Slingshot">Slingshots</a> (2), 3-bank <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Drop_Target">drop&nbsp;targets</a> (2), <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Standup_Target">Standup&nbsp;targets</a> (2), <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Kick-out_Hole">Kick-out&nbsp;holes</a> (2), <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Captive_Ball">Captive&nbsp;ball</a> (1), <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Spinning_Target">Spinning&nbsp;target</a> (1). Upper left lane has a unique <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Tilt_Rollover">tilt&nbsp;rollover</a>.<br><br>Sound: 3 chimes, <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Knocker">knocker</a>.<P></td></tr>
<tr><td width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Design by: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline><span title="Click here to perform a search for all pinball games that 'Tony&nbsp;Kraemer' was connected with."><a href="search.pl?searchtype=advanced&amp;ppl=Tony%20Kraemer">Tony&nbsp;Kraemer</a></span></td></tr>
<tr><td width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Art by: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline><span title="Click here to perform a search for all pinball games that 'Christian&nbsp;Marche' was connected with."><a href="search.pl?searchtype=advanced&amp;ppl=Christian%20Marche">Christian&nbsp;Marche</a></span></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Notes: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>Also released in a solid state version as <span title="Click here to open a new window and display Williams' 1977 'Hot Tip'"><a target="game3163" href="machine.cgi?id=3163">Williams' 1977 'Hot Tip'</a></span>.  Bonus and <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Drop_Target">drop&nbsp;target</a> values are 10 times the values on the solid state version. Other differences:<br><br><a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#EM">EM</a> 10-point rebounds are 500-points on <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#SS">SS</a> version. <br><a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#EM">EM</a> <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Spinning_Target">spinning&nbsp;target</a> value = 1000 when lit with no bonus added when spinning; <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#SS">SS</a> value is 100 when lit with 1 bonus added on every 5th spin.<br>All other values are the same as the solid state version.<br><br>Production Floor Records for Hot Tip EM:<br>Production Start Date: Jun-27-1977<br>Production End Date: Dec-5-1977<br>Production Floor Quantity: 1300<br>First ship date: Sep-14-1977<br>Last ship date: Jan-11-1978<br><br>Product History Record for Hot Tip EM: <br>Quantity produced for USA/Canada: 1003*<br>Quantity produced for export: 297*<br>Total quantity produced: 1300*<br>Price to Distributor: $970.00<br>*These quantities may be sales estimates.<P></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" align=right valign=baseline><b>Photos in: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>
Mike Pacak's Pinball Flyer Reference Book G-R<br>
</td></tr>
